stylometry: The trade off a manger must consider when dealing with lines is that if you hire another worker or put another worker on shift to deal with more customers then you need to pay that worker to work that extra time therefore rising your costs, but if you do that you might be able to serve more customers therefore making you more money in the end. The costs you must consider are; employment cost, cost of people waiting in line, and service cost. The objective would be to make the choice that brings you in the most money, whether that be paying less for one worker or deciding if that additional worker will overall serve enough additional customers to bring in more money. The objective is to bring in the most amount of money with the minimal amount of costs.
